sentences: Known for a vintage sound that incorporates elements of doo-wop, classic R&B, garage psych, and surf, Shannon and the Clams has drawn comparisons to both Buddy Holly and 1960s girl groups.
They are also said to love "music from '50s oldies to '80s punk".
In 2011, the group followed up with their sophomore effort, Sleep Talk.
Their third album, Dreams in the Rat House, was released in May 2013.
Their album Gone by the Dawn is described by Still in Rock as "the most beautiful manifestation in recent years of what I would call the 'Elvis Presley culture'".
